# Rhino Player — Cursor / agent context (compact)

## Purpose

- **Rhino Player**: mpv-backed media player for Linux (GNOME, Ubuntu, and similar) with **GTK4 / libadwaita** UI, implemented in **Rust**, targeting a **statically linked** distributable when feasible.
- **Product context**: `docs/product-and-use-cases.md` (use cases and feature map). Behavior is specified in `docs/` first, then implemented. Copyright © Peter Adrianov, 2026; see root `COPYRIGHT` and the About dialog.

## Directories

- `build.rs` — Linux: embeds `DT_RUNPATH` for `/usr/local/lib/<multiarch>` and `/usr/local/lib` so a locally built `libmpv` (e.g. VapourSynth) is preferred over the distro copy without `LD_LIBRARY_PATH`.
- `data/` — Freedesktop assets: `data/icons` (hicolor, `source/*` design + `rebuild-png-assets.sh`; see `data/icons/README.md`), `data/vs` (bundled `rhino_60_mvtools_multicore.vpy` / `rhino_60_mvtools.vpy` + [VapourSynth](https://www.vapoursynth.com/) notes; see `data/vs/README.md`), `data/applications/*.desktop`, `data/metainfo` (AppStream), `install-to-user-dirs.sh` (installs to `~/.local/share` for shell/taskbar icon). Index: `data/README.md`.
- `docs/` — Feature specs **before** implementation. Index: `docs/README.md`. One file per feature area under `docs/features/`. Product and use cases: `docs/product-and-use-cases.md`.
- `src/` — `main.rs` (entry + locale), `lib.rs`, `sched.rs` (Unix `setpriority` / nice + Linux `ioprio_set` best-effort I/O at startup, from `main` before GTK), `app.rs` (GTK shell, `GtkWindowHandle` on `ToolbarView` content for move-from-video, `APP_ID`, bottom-bar prev/play/next + seek + times + **Close video** (`app.close-video`), header sound popover: volume + audio tracks + main menu **Open** / **Move to Trash** (local file) / **Preferences** → **Smooth video (60 FPS)** (VapourSynth) + script picker, `db::init` on startup, `eof-reached` → `sibling_advance`), `audio_tracks.rs` (mpv `track-list` + `aid`, radio list in sound popover), `icons.rs` (hicolor search path for `cargo run`), `db.rs` (SQLite `rhino.sqlite`: history, `settings` kv: `video_smooth_60` / `video_vs_path`, media duration/thumbs), `video_pref.rs` (mpv `video-sync=audio` + optional `vf` from `db::VideoPrefs`, VapourSynth path or bundled `data/vs/rhino_60_mvtools_multicore.vpy` / `rhino_60_mvtools.vpy`), `mpv_embed.rs` (libmpv `RenderContext` + `GLArea`, `apply_mpv_video` after init, `commit_quit`), `paths.rs` (XDG config, mpv `watch_later`, bundled `.vpy`), `history.rs` (recent list via `db`), `media_probe.rs` (`remove_continue_entry` = resume clear + history remove, card data, libmpv `vo=image` + quit thumb), `continue_undo.rs` (session snackbar **Undo**: list-remove vs **trash** + untrash), `trash_xdg.rs` (Freedesktop `Trash` locate + restore from `files/`), `sibling_advance.rs` (next/prev local file in folder + sibling order; EOF + bottom bar), `video_ext.rs` (shared `SUFFIX` list for **Open** dialog + `sibling_advance` folder scan), `recent_view.rs` (continue grid, card hover: **trash** + **remove**, spacer `dbl`→fullscreen, session undo), `time.rs` (time formatting + tests), `theme.rs` (CSS).
- `tests/` — Integration tests (e.g. libmpv smoke).

## Workflow

- **Document-first**: see `.cursor/rules/document-first.mdc`. Do not implement substantial features without an up-to-date `docs/features/…` file (status, short/long description, specification).

## Conventions

- Keep `.cursorrules` and `docs/README.md` feature list aligned with what exists in the tree.
- Prefer clear module boundaries: UI (GTK/Adwaita), mpv control, platform (DBus, portals), persistence (settings, session).
- **Clippy:** run `cargo qcheck` (or `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features`); do not add `#[allow(clippy::…)]`—fix by refactoring (see `.cursor/rules/clippy-no-suppress.mdc`).
- **Complexity and module shape:** there is no Ruby-style `AbcSize` in Rust; use Clippy (see `clippy.toml`, `cargo qcheck`) and follow `.cursor/rules/complexity-and-module-design.mdc` (cognitive-complexity gate; if a feature touches **>6 files**, refactor toward SOLID / single reason to change per module).
- **UI / IO timing:** prefer event subscriptions over periodic polls; see `.cursor/rules/events-over-polling.mdc`.
- Name length: prefer short, clear identifiers (2–3 words) for new types and functions, consistent with the rest of the file.
